verbose_text: Activation of stimulatory G proteins (Gs) coupled to beta2 receptors induces an increase in intracellular cAMP leading to the activation of protein kinase A (PKA), with the participation of the Ikappabeta / NF-kappabeta pathway to induce anti-inflammatory effects in monocytic cells [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
